Package: kat
Title: What the package does (short line)
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: "Stephen Henderson <s.henderson@ucl.ac.uk> [aut, cre]"
Description: The kat package is designed for the analysis of cancer mutation
    patterns from genomic VCF or MAF files (or similar formats). It has several
    summary statistics functions, plus analyses for NMF, sliding windows, and
    scan (or sliding window) statistics. It was designed with a special
    interest in kataegesis mutation analysis (showers of mutations).
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0)
License: MIT
LazyData: true
